    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change Universal Credit so second parent earnings don't affect family\u2019s payment",
        "additional_details": "Many parents work hard to give their children a better life, but Universal Credit cuts payments when the second parent earns extra. Families often feel punished for doing the right thing, children can face poverty, and stress can rise at home. We want the Government to change UC so a second parent\u2019s earnings do not reduce the family\u2019s payment.",
        "background": "We want the Government to change Universal Credit so that any earnings of a second parent in a couple do not reduce the overall family\u2019s payment. The current policy discourages people from taking up work.",
